This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of single image rain removal, which is a typical inverse problem in computer vision. The paper also proposes a deep learning technique to solve this problem. 

The paper also involves the use of semi-supervised learning, which is a machine learning technique that combines both labeled and unlabeled data for training. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Additionally, the paper involves the use of image processing techniques, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
